node.text:
I like to think that I've got much better at dealing with changes, but unfortunately it's something I still struggle with. I moved recently and although I'm happy for this new chapter and the new opportunities ahead, I can't help but feel so many mixed emotions for everything that's been going on. Saying goodbye to our little apartment that was our refuge for one year and a half during a pandemic was hard, even if it sounds silly. 

I miss drawing so much and I know everything will find its place and I'll feel more like myself once I take my time to start creating art again. I also look forward to building my new studio! 💕 Hopefully bigger and nicer than the previous one heh.

Thanks for your kind messages, your replies to my stories and your enthusiasm, I love reading you!! 

Happy weekend ❤️
.
.
.
#artstudio #moving

node.text:
Lil process video testing some pens @morfoneart sent me recently! Acrylic markers are always so much fun and these are no exception, they work super similar to Poscas (but are way more affordable) and they are veryyy opaque. Colors are really lovely as well, you get a cool mix of pastel and dark tones in this 24 set! Really love all the green shades 💖  The broad nib is not ideal for little details but it’s awesome for large areas!

I’ll post some pictures of other stuff I painted with these markers in the upcoming days 🥰

Thank you @morfoneart! 
.
.
.
#acrylicpen #morofone #morfoneart #sketchbook #traditionalart #sketchbookpage #goose #acrylicmarkers #videoprocess #drawingprocess #painting

node.text:
Our graphic novel Primer released exactly one year ago! ✨here’s something I finished today to celebrate her first anniversary :D

I worked on this book for more than a year and it was one of the (if not THE) toughest and most rewarding projects I've been part of! I learned a bunch about making comics and it also brought a lot of exciting opportunities for my career, and for that I'll be forever grateful 💕

When I was doing my character design test to get the job back in 2018, @donsrice encouraged me to draw a 3 page comic about Primer to send to DC as well, alongside my character designs (swipe left to see them) we wrote together a silly script and I tried to pull off something presentable in just one weekend. I don't think I had posted these before, it's so nice to look back and see how everything turned out in the end, despite the doubts and fears!

Thank you @officialjennifermuro and @krajewski_tom ! And thank you @suddenchad @diegslopez @editorhat and @m_is_for_michele ❤️also thanks so much to everyone who bought a copy and who showed enthusiasm, support and love for this story and these characters, you are an essential part of the Primer family!!
.
.
.
#dcprimer #dccomics #ashleyrayburn #comics

This book is a guide full of resources, sketches, insights and ideas for character design from some of the coolest artists in the industry. It's truly a gorgeous book and I loved working on it 💕

You can grab your copy on 3dtotal shop! Link is in my bio 
Thank you @3dtotal 🌈✨
